						<summary>

						<p>The record is not dated and is much damaged. It refers itself to the reign of the Chāḷukya king <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalladēva</hi> ruling from <hi rend="bold">Kalyāna.</hi> It mentions the Jaina teachers <hi rend="bold">Nayakīrtidēva</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Indrakīrti,</hi> the prince <hi rend="bold">Kumāra-Tailapadēva</hi> and his subordinates <hi rend="bold">Mācharasa, Saṅkarasa</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Muddarasa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
